  25 class Finder(object):
  26 
  27     """
  28     A cross-platform Finder for locating python and other executables.
  29 
  30     Searches for python and other specified binaries starting in *path*, if supplied,
  31     but searching the bin path of ``sys.executable`` if *system* is ``True``, and then
  32     searching in the ``os.environ['PATH']`` if *global_search* is ``True``.  When *global_search*
  33     is ``False``, this search operation is restricted to the allowed locations of
  34     *path* and *system*.
  35     """
  36 
  37     def __init__(
  38         self,
  39         path=None,
  40         system=False,
  41         global_search=True,
  42         ignore_unsupported=True,
  43         sort_by_path=False,
  44     ):
  45         # type: (Optional[str], bool, bool, bool, bool) -> None
  46         """Create a new :class:`~pythonfinder.pythonfinder.Finder` instance.
  47 
  48         :param path: A bin-directory search location, defaults to None
  49         :param path: str, optional
  50         :param system: Whether to include the bin-dir of ``sys.executable``, defaults to False
  51         :param system: bool, optional
  52         :param global_search: Whether to search the global path from os.environ, defaults to True
  53         :param global_search: bool, optional
  54         :param ignore_unsupported: Whether to ignore unsupported python versions, if False, an
  55             error is raised, defaults to True
  56         :param ignore_unsupported: bool, optional
  57         :param bool sort_by_path: Whether to always sort by path
  58         :returns: a :class:`~pythonfinder.pythonfinder.Finder` object.
  59         """
  60 
  61         self.path_prepend = path  # type: Optional[str]
  62         self.global_search = global_search  # type: bool
  63         self.system = system  # type: bool
  64         self.sort_by_path = sort_by_path  # type: bool
  65         self.ignore_unsupported = ignore_unsupported  # type: bool
  66         self._system_path = None  # type: Optional[SystemPath]
  67         self._windows_finder = None  # type: Optional[WindowsFinder]
  68 
  69     def __hash__(self):
  70         # type: () -> int
  71         return hash(
  72             (self.path_prepend, self.system, self.global_search, self.ignore_unsupported)
  73         )
  74 
  75     def __eq__(self, other):
  76         # type: (Any) -> bool
  77         return self.__hash__() == other.__hash__()
  78 
  79     def create_system_path(self):
  80         # type: () -> SystemPath
  81         pyfinder_path = importlib.import_module("pythonfinder.models.path")
  82         return pyfinder_path.SystemPath.create(
  83             path=self.path_prepend,
  84             system=self.system,
  85             global_search=self.global_search,
  86             ignore_unsupported=self.ignore_unsupported,
  87         )
  88 
  89     def reload_system_path(self):
  90         # type: () -> None
  91         """
  92         Rebuilds the base system path and all of the contained finders within it.
  93 
  94         This will re-apply any changes to the environment or any version changes on the system.
  95         """
  96 
  97         if self._system_path is not None:
  98             self._system_path = self._system_path.clear_caches()
  99             self._system_path = None
 100         pyfinder_path = importlib.import_module("pythonfinder.models.path")
 101         six.moves.reload_module(pyfinder_path)
 102         self._system_path = self.create_system_path()
 103 
 104     def rehash(self):
 105         # type: () -> "Finder"
 106         if not self._system_path:
 107             self._system_path = self.create_system_path()
 108         self.find_all_python_versions.cache_clear()
 109         self.find_python_version.cache_clear()
 110         if self._windows_finder is not None:
 111             self._windows_finder = None
 112         filter_pythons.cache_clear()
 113         self.reload_system_path()
 114         return self
 115 
 116     @property
 117     def system_path(self):
 118         # type: () -> SystemPath
 119         if self._system_path is None:
 120             self._system_path = self.create_system_path()
 121         return self._system_path
 122 
 123     @property
 124     def windows_finder(self):
 125         # type: () -> Optional[WindowsFinder]
 126         if os.name == "nt" and not self._windows_finder:
 127             from .models import WindowsFinder
 128 
 129             self._windows_finder = WindowsFinder()
 130         return self._windows_finder
 131 
 132     def which(self, exe):
 133         # type: (str) -> Optional[PathEntry]
 134         return self.system_path.which(exe)

 136     @classmethod
 137     def parse_major(
 138         cls,
 139         major,  # type: Optional[str]
 140         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 141         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 142         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 143         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 144         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 145     ):
 146         # type: (...) -> Dict[str, Union[int, str, bool, None]]
 147         from .models import PythonVersion
 148 
 149         major_is_str = major and isinstance(major, six.string_types)
 150         is_num = (
 151             major
 152             and major_is_str
 153             and all(part.isdigit() for part in major.split(".")[:2])
 154         )
 155         major_has_arch = (
 156             arch is None
 157             and major
 158             and major_is_str
 159             and "-" in major
 160             and major[0].isdigit()
 161         )
 162         name = None
 163         if major and major_has_arch:
 164             orig_string = "{0!s}".format(major)
 165             major, _, arch = major.rpartition("-")
 166             if arch:
 167                 arch = arch.lower().lstrip("x").replace("bit", "")
 168                 if not (arch.isdigit() and (int(arch) & int(arch) - 1) == 0):
 169                     major = orig_string
 170                     arch = None
 171                 else:
 172                     arch = "{0}bit".format(arch)
 173             try:
 174                 version_dict = PythonVersion.parse(major)
 175             except (ValueError, InvalidPythonVersion):
 176                 if name is None:
 177                     name = "{0!s}".format(major)
 178                     major = None
 179                 version_dict = {}
 180         elif major and major[0].isalpha():
 181             return {"major": None, "name": major, "arch": arch}
 182         elif major and is_num:
 183             match = version_re.match(major)
 184             version_dict = match.groupdict() if match else {}  # type: ignore
 185             version_dict.update(
 186                 {
 187                     "is_prerelease": bool(version_dict.get("prerel", False)),
 188                     "is_devrelease": bool(version_dict.get("dev", False)),
 189                 }
 190             )
 191         else:
 192             version_dict = {
 193                 "major": major,
 194                 "minor": minor,
 195                 "patch": patch,
 196                 "pre": pre,
 197                 "dev": dev,
 198                 "arch": arch,
 199             }
 200         if not version_dict.get("arch") and arch:
 201             version_dict["arch"] = arch
 202         version_dict["minor"] = (
 203             int(version_dict["minor"]) if version_dict.get("minor") is not None else minor
 204         )
 205         version_dict["patch"] = (
 206             int(version_dict["patch"]) if version_dict.get("patch") is not None else patch
 207         )
 208         version_dict["major"] = (
 209             int(version_dict["major"]) if version_dict.get("major") is not None else major
 210         )
 211         if not (version_dict["major"] or version_dict.get("name")):
 212             version_dict["major"] = major
 213             if name:
 214                 version_dict["name"] = name
 215         return version_dict
 216 
 217     @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 218     def find_python_version(
 219         self,
 220         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 221         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 222         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 223         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 224         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 225         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 226         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 227         sort_by_path=False,  # type: bool
 228     ):
 229         # type: (...) -> Optional[PathEntry]
 230         """
 231         Find the python version which corresponds most closely to the version requested.
 232 
 233         :param Union[str, int] major: The major version to look for, or the full version, or the name of the target version.
 234         :param Optional[int] minor: The minor version. If provided, disables string-based lookups from the major version field.
 235         :param Optional[int] patch: The patch version.
 236         :param Optional[bool] pre: If provided, specifies whether to search pre-releases.
 237         :param Optional[bool] dev: If provided, whether to search dev-releases.
 238         :param Optional[str] arch: If provided, which architecture to search.
 239         :param Optional[str] name: *Name* of the target python, e.g. ``anaconda3-5.3.0``
 240         :param bool sort_by_path: Whether to sort by path -- default sort is by version(default: False)
 241         :return: A new *PathEntry* pointer at a matching python version, if one can be located.
 242         :rtype: :class:`pythonfinder.models.path.PathEntry`
 243         """
 244 
 245         minor = int(minor) if minor is not None else minor
 246         patch = int(patch) if patch is not None else patch
 247 
 248         version_dict = {
 249             "minor": minor,
 250             "patch": patch,
 251             "name": name,
 252             "arch": arch,
 253         }  # type: Dict[str, Union[str, int, Any]]
 254 
 255         if (
 256             isinstance(major, six.string_types)
 257             and pre is None
 258             and minor is None
 259             and dev is None
 260             and patch is None
 261         ):
 262             version_dict = self.parse_major(major, minor=minor, patch=patch, arch=arch)
 263             major = version_dict["major"]
 264             minor = version_dict.get("minor", minor)  # type: ignore
 265             patch = version_dict.get("patch", patch)  # type: ignore
 266             arch = version_dict.get("arch", arch)  # type: ignore
 267             name = version_dict.get("name", name)  # type: ignore
 268             _pre = version_dict.get("is_prerelease", pre)
 269             pre = bool(_pre) if _pre is not None else pre
 270             _dev = version_dict.get("is_devrelease", dev)
 271             dev = bool(_dev) if _dev is not None else dev
 272             if "architecture" in version_dict and isinstance(
 273                 version_dict["architecture"], six.string_types
 274             ):
 275                 arch = version_dict["architecture"]  # type: ignore
 276         if os.name == "nt" and self.windows_finder is not None:
 277             found = self.windows_finder.find_python_version(
 278                 major=major,
 279                 minor=minor,
 280                 patch=patch,
 281                 pre=pre,
 282                 dev=dev,
 283                 arch=arch,
 284                 name=name,
 285             )
 286             if found:
 287                 return found
 288         return self.system_path.find_python_version(
 289             major=major,
 290             minor=minor,
 291             patch=patch,
 292             pre=pre,
 293             dev=dev,
 294             arch=arch,
 295             name=name,
 296             sort_by_path=self.sort_by_path,
 297         )
 298 
 299     @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 300     def find_all_python_versions(
 301         self,
 302         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 303         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 304         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 305         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 306         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 307         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 308         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 309     ):
 310         # type: (...) -> List[PathEntry]
 311         version_sort = operator.attrgetter("as_python.version_sort")
 312         python_version_dict = getattr(self.system_path, "python_version_dict", {})
 313         if python_version_dict:
 314             paths = (
 315                 path
 316                 for version in python_version_dict.values()
 317                 for path in version
 318                 if path is not None and path.as_python
 319             )
 320             path_list = sorted(paths, key=version_sort, reverse=True)
 321             return path_list
 322         versions = self.system_path.find_all_python_versions(
 323             major=major, minor=minor, patch=patch, pre=pre, dev=dev, arch=arch, name=name
 324         )
 325         if not isinstance(versions, Iterable):
 326             versions = [versions]
 327         # This list has already been mostly sorted on windows, we don't need to reverse it again
 328         path_list = sorted(versions, key=version_sort, reverse=True)
 329         path_map = {}  # type: Dict[str, PathEntry]
 330         for path in path_list:
 331             try:
 332                 resolved_path = path.path.resolve()
 333             except OSError:
 334                 resolved_path = path.path.absolute()
 335             if not path_map.get(resolved_path.as_posix()):
 336                 path_map[resolved_path.as_posix()] = path
 337         return path_list
